# Repository Patterns

Repositories handle all Prisma/database operations.

## Structure

```typescript
import prisma from "@/shared/database/prisma";
import { Type1, Type2 } from "@/shared/types/{feature}.types";

class FeatureRepository {
  async findAll(): Promise<Model[]> {
    return await prisma.model.findMany();
  }

  async findById(id: string): Promise<Model | null> {
    return await prisma.model.findUnique({ where: { id } });
  }

  async create(data: CreateRequest): Promise<Model> {
    return await prisma.model.create({ data });
  }

  async update(id: string, data: UpdateRequest): Promise<Model | null> {
    try {
      return await prisma.model.update({ where: { id }, data });
    } catch (error) {
      return null;
    }
  }

  async delete(id: string): Promise<boolean> {
    try {
      await prisma.model.delete({ where: { id } });
      return true;
    } catch (error) {
      return false;
    }
  }
}

export default new FeatureRepository();
```

## Rules

Repositories MUST:
- Import `prisma` from `@/shared/database/prisma`
- Handle ONLY database operations
- Return `null` for not found (instead of throwing)
- Return `boolean` for delete operations
- Convert date strings to Date objects before saving

Repositories MUST NOT:
- Contain business logic
- Format response data
- Handle HTTP concerns

## Date Handling

```typescript
// ✅ Convert string dates to Date objects for Prisma
async create(data: CreateRequest): Promise<Model> {
  return await prisma.model.create({
    data: {
      ...data,
      birthDate: new Date(data.birthDate),
      dateField: data.dateField ? new Date(data.dateField) : null,
    },
  });
}
```

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ✅ Return null on not found
async update(id: string, data: UpdateRequest): Promise<Model | null> {
  try {
    return await prisma.model.update({ where: { id }, data });
  } catch (error) {
    return null;  // Not found or update failed
  }
}

// ✅ Return boolean for delete
async delete(id: string): Promise<boolean> {
  try {
    await prisma.model.delete({ where: { id } });
    return true;
  } catch (error) {
    return false;  // Not found or delete failed
  }
}
```
